<!--
  ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
  HOW TO USE IN PROTEGE
  ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
  1. Open Protege
  2. File → Open → select this file (iiitb_institution.owl)
  3. Click the "Classes" tab → you will see University, Course, Faculty etc.
  4. Click "Object Properties" tab → hasCourse, hasFaculty etc.
  5. Click "Individuals by class" tab → IIITB, all courses, faculty listed

  TO INTEGRATE INTO MASTER OWL:
  Option A (Merge):
    File → Merge Ontology → select iisc.owl, nitk.owl etc.
    All individuals from all files appear in one graph.

  Option B (Import):
    In your master.owl add:
      owl:imports <http://example.org/iiitb>
    Then repeat for other source ontologies.

  Option C (Jena Fuseki - recommended for SPARQL):
    Upload each .owl file as a separate Named Graph.
    Run federated SPARQL queries across all graphs.
  ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
-->
